3) Why I chose Fleetwood Mac and rejected the Beach Boys compilation: because my explicit criterion is enjoyment of listening to CDs (not a stated genre bias), I selected the CD whose format and production style most directly reward attentive, album-style CD listening. The Fleetwood Mac compilation represents an AOR/classic-rock body of work whose layered arrangements, dynamic contrasts, and studio clarity are particularly well showcased on a CD and support a cohesive listening experience. By contrast, the Beach Boys compilation is a strong singles anthology celebrating historic pop hits and harmonies, but as a hits collection it is less oriented toward the album-focused, production-rich listening experience that I — as someone who enjoys engaging with CDs — prioritized in making this choice.

