The user updates his self-description as follows: I prefer CDs that foreground tight, lush vocal harmonies, concise melody-driven songs, and the warm, intimate character of early‑60s pop production — the kind of hits‑focused compilation where each track is immediate andvocally prominent (for example, The Beach Boys’ vocal arrangements and vintage timbres). I enjoy listening to CDs very much and appreciate releases that reward focused, track‑by‑track listening on a physical disc. From my past note that I enjoy CDs, I keep the love of the format and attentive listening. I dislike CDs that prioritize sprawling album‑oriented rock polish over clear melodies: dense, reverb‑heavy AOR production, lengthy sequencing, or layered instrumental textures that push vocals into the background are generally not to my taste.

