3) Choice rationale
Tumbleweed Connection best aligns with my stated aesthetics: it emphasizes intimate, midrange‑forward lead vocals and rich harmonies, preserves tape transients and headroom, and presents an ensemble‑first acoustic palette (acoustic guitar, pedal steel, upright bass) with tasteful keys and focused imaging. Those are precisely the attributes I favor—warm analogue character, multitracked harmony prominence, restrained low end and natural dynamics—without the arena production elements I dislike.
